    <h1>About</h1>
    <h3>What Is FI?</h3>
    <p>
      FI stands for Financial Independence.<br/>
      Financial Independence means having enough assests to sustain your
      living expenses indefinately.<br/>
      This is the point where you could stop receiving an income and never run out of money.<br/>
      Note this doesn't necessarily mean that you'll stop working,
      but it simply means you no longer need to work for money.<br/>
      Freeing you pursue what ever interests inspire you.
    </p>
    <p>
      In order to reach FI you need to spend less than you earn and invest the difference wisely.
    </p>
    <h3>About The Time To FI Calculator</h3>
    <p>
      This calculator is a simple tool to help you estimate when you will reach FI.<br/>
      Based on your current spending, income, and net worth it will determine when you will reach FI.<br/>
    </p>
    <h3>About The Time Added To FI Calculator</h3>
    <p>
      This calculator is a simple tool to help you make smart decisions concerning your path to FI.<br/>
      It references your current time to FI and figures how much time will be added or removed
      based on changed monthly spending, changed monthly income, or a one time expense. <br/>
    </p>
